Federal Service for State Registration, Cadastre and Cartography
Федеральная служба государственной регистрации, кадастра и картографии
Agency seal

Agency flag
Agency overview
Formed 9 March 2004
Preceding agencies
  • Federal Agency for Geodesy and Cartography (Roskartografiya)
  • Federal Real Estate Cadastre Agency (Rosnedvizhimost)
Jurisdiction Government of Russia
Headquarters Chistoprudny Boulevard 6/19, Moscow
Minister responsible
  • Victoria V. Abramchenko, Deputy Minister of Economic Development
Website www.rosreestr.ru

The Federal Service for State Registration, Cadastre and Cartography (Rosreestr) (Russian: Федеральная служба государственной регистрации, кадастра и картографии) (prior to December 30, 2008, Federal Registration Service) is a federal agency in Russia, responsible for the organization of the Unified State Register of Rights on Real Estate and Transactions (Russian: Единый государственный реестр прав на недвижимое имущество и сделок с ним), as well as the spatial data infrastructure of the Russian Federation.

According to the amendments to the list of names and abbreviations of the federal bodies of executive power (the order of the Presidential Administration of Russia and the Government of Russia of July 16, 2008 № 943/788) of 2 March 2009 number P41-6596 abbreviation of the Federal Service for State Registration, Cadastre and Cartography - Rosreestr.
